Why Docker is preferred for modern apps


Faster deployments


Better resource utilization


Easy scaling


Perfect for microservices


Works well with CI/CD (Jenkins)



When to use VM instead


Need strong isolation


Running different OS kernels


Legacy applications


Compliance/security requirements



Interview-Perfect Answer (Memorize)

â€œVirtual machines virtualize hardware and include a full operating system for each instance, which makes them heavy and slower to start. Docker containers virtualize the OS, share the host kernel, and are lightweight, start quickly, and use fewer resources, making them ideal for scalable cloud applications.â€


Bonus One-Liner (Senior-Level)

â€œContainers trade some isolation for speed and efficiency, while VMs trade efficiency for stronger isolation.â€


